# Architecture Reviewer

Auto-scan the project and review architecture against system design principles.

## Scan Process
1. Read config files (package.json, docker-compose, Dockerfile, go.mod, etc.)
2. Identify API routes, DB configs, cache configs, queue configs
3. Map discovered components and dependencies

## Review Checklist

### Scalability
- [ ] Stateless app servers (no local session storage)?
- [ ] DB scaling strategy (replicas for reads, sharding for writes)?
- [ ] Cache layer for read-heavy paths (90%+ hit rate = 10x DB capacity)?
- [ ] Async processing for write-heavy/long tasks?
- [ ] CDN for static assets?

### Reliability
- [ ] No single points of failure?
- [ ] Circuit breaker / retry + backoff for external calls?
- [ ] Graceful degradation under load?
- [ ] Health checks (readiness + liveness)?
- [ ] DR strategy (RPO/RTO defined)?

### Data Architecture
- [ ] DB choice matches access patterns (SQL for joins, NoSQL for K/V)?
- [ ] Indexes cover hot queries (B-tree for range, hash for equality)?
- [ ] Replication/backup strategy?
- [ ] No N+1 query patterns?

### Communication
- [ ] Right protocol per use case (REST for public, gRPC for internal, WS for real-time)?
- [ ] Async where sync unnecessary?
- [ ] Idempotency for non-safe operations (POST with idempotency key)?

### Security
- [ ] AuthN/AuthZ implemented?
- [ ] Rate limiting on public endpoints?
- [ ] Input validation at boundaries?
- [ ] Secrets in env vars, not code?
- [ ] TLS for all external communication?

### Observability
- [ ] Structured logging?
- [ ] Metrics (latency p95/p99, error rate, throughput)?
- [ ] Distributed tracing for multi-service?
- [ ] Alerting on SLO violations?

## Output Format

| # | Category | Severity | Finding | Recommendation |
|---|----------|----------|---------|----------------|

**Severity levels:** Critical (fix now) | High (fix soon) | Medium (plan fix) | Low (nice to have)

End with: Strengths, Top 3 Improvements, Architecture Score (X/10).

